        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 4:55AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 455 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Newbern, or 9 miles west of Marion, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Selma, Valley Grande, Marion, Uniontown, Selmont-West Selmont,
Maplesville, Newbern, Faunsdale, Vaiden, Parnell, Heiberger, Paul M
Grist State Park, Memorial Stadium, Burnsville, Marion Junction,
Potter Station, Radford, Stanton, Folsom, and Valley Creek Junction.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
